=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Slew_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.5304
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8179
  pitch_clarity: 28.1423
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -13.9049
  resonance_freq: 753.6621

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Slew Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Slew.html
// Tags: Slew, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{
    z = LFPulse.ar(800);
    [z, Slew.ar(z, 4000, 4000)]
}.plot)



Has the effect of removing transients and higher frequencies.
(
{

    z = Saw.ar(800, mul: 0.2);
    Slew.ar(z, 400, 400)

}.play
)
